"Basic_Lan_Help_Head":"<div class='modal-header'><button data-dismiss='modal' class='close' type='button'>&times;</button><h3>Private IP Setting Guide</h3></div>",
"Basic_Lan_Help_Body":"<div class='modal-body'><h4>Introduction</h4><br/><p>The setup section is the IP information distributed by the gateway to your local network (computers connected to your gateway).</p><hr><h4>How to configure LAN IP</h4><br/><p>Private LAN IP Address:  The private LAN IP Address is the gateway's LAN IP address. PC connected to CM would acquire DHCP IP belong to the same subnet as the CM's private LAN IP address.</p><p>Subnet Mask:  This field defines the subnet used by the CM's DHCP server for private LAN address.</p><p>Buttons for Enable/Disable LAN DHCP:  Here you can enable/disable the DHCP server feature for private LAN IP to assign IP addresses to the LAN client PCs.</p><p>Button for DHCP reservation:  This button would pop up a sub window to allow end users to setup the DHCP IP reservation through 'Manually Add Client' table.</p><p>Lease Time:  It's the IP lease time assigned by the LAN DHCP server.</p><p>DHCP Start IP:  This defines the first available LAN IP Address that will be assigned by the LAN DHCP.</p><p>DHCP End IP:  This defines the last available LAN IP Address that will be assigned by the LAN DHCP. The number of IP addresses between the DHCP Start IP and DHCP End IP will determine the DHCP IP Address pool size.</p><hr/><h4>Buttons</h4><br><p>This <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn btn-primary'>Save changes</a> should save the data and submit the form.</p><p>This <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn'>Cancel</a> should reset the all data.</p><p>This <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn'>Help</a> should show the configure guide.</p></div>",

