"Basic_Pf_Help_Head":"<div class='modal-header'><button data-dismiss='modal' class='close' type='button'>&times;</button><h3>Port Forwarding Rules Setting Guide</h3></div>",
"Basic_Pf_Help_Body":"<div class='modal-body'><h4>Introduction</h4><br/><p>Forwarding is used to redirect the inbound traffic to the appropriate server(s) or specifically identified application(s) in the internal network.</p><hr><h4>How to configure port forwarding</h4><br/><p>Enable/Disable buttons for 'All Port Forwarding Rules':  Enable/Disable the add/edit/delete of port forwarding rule table.</p><p>Add button:  When the Add button is pressed, a pop-up window 'Add a rule for port forwarding service' table would show up with the following fields for configuration.</p><p>Common Application:  If end users want to define a rule for well-known application, they can try to pick up the application from the drag-down menu in the field. After a well-know application is selected, the 'Application Name', 'Protocol' and 'public Port Range' would be filled automatically.</p><p>Application Name:  This field is used to identify this rule. If end users select a well-known application from 'common Application' field, this field would be auto-filled and cannot be modified.</p><p>Protocol:  This field defines the protocol type (TCP, UDP, TCP/UDP, GRE, or ESP) which will be used for this forwarding rule.</p><p>Public Port Range: This field defines the ports that users on the Internet will use to connect to the LAN service you create with this forwarding rule. The assignable ports are between 1 and 65535.</p><p>Private Port Range:  This field defines the port range on the LAN PC that this rule will forward traffic to. The size of the private port range must match the size of the public port range, and is automatically calculated for you.</p><p>Local IP Address: This field defines the computer you want the traffic to be forwarded to.</p><hr/><h4>Buttons</h4><br><p>This <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn btn-info'>Add Rule</a> should add a new rule.</p><p>This <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn btn-primary'>Save changes</a> should save the data and submit the form.</p><p>This <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn'>Manage</a> should edit a rule.</p><p>This <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn btn-danger'>Remove</a> should delete a rule.</p><p>This <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn'>Help</a> should show the configure guide.</p></div>",

