"Basic_Pt_Help_Head":"<div class='modal-header'><button data-dismiss='modal' class='close' type='button'>&times;</button><h3>Port Triggering Rules Setting Guide</h3></div>",
"Basic_Pt_Help_Body":"<div class='modal-body'><h4>Introduction</h4><br/><p>Port Triggering is used to allow computers on your local area network to be accessed by sessions triggered by specific applications on the Internet. The triggered sessions are initiated by the application on the Internet when some application on your local PC tries to communication with the specific Internet server and need a third or more sessions to be created from Internet to the local PC. In this case, port triggering rule is needed to allow such session which is in the port range setup to be created from Internet to local LAN. The target port range would be open to allowed Internet triggered traffic to pass CM's firewall within the timeout time when this rule is triggered by outgoing traffic which matches the trigger port range define in the rule.</p><hr><h4>How to configure port triggering</h4><br/><p>Enable/Disable buttons for 'All Port Triggering Rules':  Enable/Disable the add/edit/delete of port triggering rule table.To edit an existing rule, select the rule from the port triggering rule table, and click edit. Make sure the Enable box is checked when you wish to enforce a specific port triggering rule.</p><p>Application Name: This field is used to identify this port triggering rule.</p><p>Trigger Port Range: This field defines the outgoing port range which will trigger this rule to open the target port range for incoming traffic sessions.</p><p>Target Port Range: This field defines the port that the incoming traffic will be forwarded to on the local client PC.</p><p>Protocol: This field defines the protocol used for this rule.</p><p>Timeout: This field defines the value of the effective time for triggered and forwarded ports.</p><hr/><h4>Buttons</h4><br><p>This <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn btn-info'>Add Rule</a> should add a new rule.</p><p>This <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn btn-primary'>Save changes</a> should save the data and submit the form.</p><p>This <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn'>Manage</a> should edit a rule.</p><p>This <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn btn-danger'>Remove</a> should delete a rule.</p><p>This <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn'>Help</a> should show the configure guide.</p></div>",

