"Basic_Dns_Help_Head":"<div class='modal-header'><button data-dismiss='modal' class='close' type='button'>&times;</button><h3>DNS Setting Guide</h3></div>",
"Basic_Dns_Help_Body":"<div class='modal-body'><h4>Introduction</h4><p>DNS is used by computers to resolve the IP address from the Full Qualified Domain Name(FQDN) address. CM would get the DNS server addresses from MSO's provisioning system. The DNS information acquired from provisioning system can be provided directly to end users' PC or CM can play as a DNS proxy and do the DNS query for the computers behind the CM.</p><hr/><h4>How to configure DNS</h4><br/><p>LAN DNS: If 'Auto' button is selected and LAN DNS Proxy Status is 'Disabled', this means the DNS server addressed used by the CM are acquired from MSO's provisioning system. If 'Manual' is selected, this means DNS server addresses used by CM would be filled by end users.</p><p>LAN DNS Proxy Status: If 'Enabled' is selected, this means CM would play as a DNS proxy server and do the DNS query to the DNS servers (provided in the setting of 'LAN DNS'). In this setting, CM's private LAN IP would be provided as the DNS server to the computers behind the CM.  If 'Disabled' is selected, CM would not play as a DNS proxy server and the DNS server addresses acquired by CM (from provisioning system or manual input) would be provided to the computers behind the CM through LAN's DHCP.</p><p>Domain Suffix:  This field defines the domain name of CM. It will be provided to computers behind the CM through LAN's DHCP.  If the proxy hostnames defined below are null, then the default FQDN would be the domain suffix only and end users can access the local web with this domain suffix. For example, if the domain suffix is hitronhub.home and proxy hostnames are null, then the FQDN for CM's local web is http://hitronhub.home.</p><p>Proxy Hostname1:  This field is in-sync with the 'Domain Suffix' setting. End users can use this setting combining with the domain suffix to form the FQDN to access CM's GUI for management, instead of using CM's LAN IP address directly.For example, if the proxy hostname1 is host1 and domain suffix is hitronhub.home, then the FQDN for local web access is http://host1.hitronhub.home.</p><p>Proxy Hostname2:  This field is in-sync with the 'Domain Suffix' setting. End users can use this setting combining with the domain suffix to form the FQDN to access CM's GUI for management, instead of using CM's LAN IP address directly.For example, if the proxy hostname2 is host2 and domain suffix is hitronhub.home, then the FQDN for local web access is http://host2.hitronhub.home.</p><p>For 'Proxy Hostname1' and 'Proxy Hostname2', these setting can only be effective when the 'LAN DNS Proxy Status' setting is 'Enabled'. If 'LAN DNS Proxy Status' setting is 'Disabled', then end users can not use FQDN formed by proxy hostnames and domain suffix for CM's GUI access, but can only use IP address for accessing GUI.</p><hr /><h4>Buttons</h4><p>This <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn btn-primary'>Save changes</a> should save the data and submit the form.</p><p>This <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn'>Cancel</a> should reset the all data.</p><p>This <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn'>Help</a> should show the configure guide.</p></div>",

