"Wireless_Basic_Help_Head":"<div class='modal-header'><button data-dismiss='modal' class='close' type=button>&times;</button><h3>Wireless Basic Setting Guide</h3>",
"Wireless_Basic_Help_Body":"<div class='modal-body'><h4>Basic Settings</h4><br/><p>2.4G/5G Tabs</strong></p><p>Switch the tab to choose which band you would like to configure.</p><p><strong>Wireless Enable</strong></p><p>Enable or disable your wireless</p><p><strong>Wireless Mode</strong></p><p>Choose the standard your device will support. If you don't know what it is, leave it to 'b/g/n mixed'.</p><p><strong>Wireless Channel</strong></p><p>Choose which radio channel your device will use. If you don't know what it is, leave it to 'auto'.</p><p><strong>WPS Enable</strong></p><p>Enable/disable Wifi-Protected-Setup support.</p><p>Wi-Fi Protected Setup is a feature that makes it easy to set up your wireless network. To use this feature, you need a wireless client thatsupports Wi-Fi Protected Setup and go to the WPS & Security. </p><hr><h4>SSID Settings</h4><br/><p><strong>Network Name(SSID)</strong></p><p>Set a network name for your wireless network.</p><p><strong> Enable </strong></p><p>Enable/disable this wireless network.</p><p><strong>Broadcast SSID</strong></p><p>Set to 'ON' to make your device able to detect your wireless network.<br/><p>Set to 'OFF' to hide your network.<br/><p><strong>WMM(QoS)</strong></p><p>Wi-Fi Multimedia (WMM) is a wireless Quality of Service(QoS)feature that improves quality for audio, video, and voice applications by prioritizing wireless traffic.</p><hr><h4>Buttons</h4><br/><p>Click <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn btn-primary'>Save changes</a> to apply the basic settings to device</p><p>Click <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn'>Cancel</a> to reset all the data.</p><p>Click <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn'>Help</a> to see this guide.</p></div>",

