"Wireless_Security_Help_Head":"<div class=\"modal-header\"><button data-dismiss=\"modal\" class=\"close\" type=\"button\">&times;</button><h3>Wireless WPS and Security Setting Guide</h3></div>",
"Wireless_Security_Help_Body":"<div class=\"modal-body\"><h4>Introduction</h4><p>The setup section is the IP information distributed by the gateway to your local network (computers connected to your gateway).</p><h4>How to configure the wireless basic settings</h4><br/><p><b>WPS Settings</b></p><p>For the WPS operation, the function of the PBC button is the same as the button on the top of the housing. If it's pressed, the device would begin the WPS negotiation process with another wireless client which run PBC mode also. </p><p>If the PIN button is pressed, the device would pop-up a dialog box for users to fill in a 8-character PIN code for WPS negotiation. At the same time, the wireless client must use the same PIN code for WPS negotiation.</p><p><b>Security Settings</b></span></p><p>Wireless Security allows you to select whether you would like to have wireless security active or not, and the type of wireless security to be used.  You can choose any of the two types of security offered:</p><p>WEP (Wired Equivalent Privacy) Encryption Strength is a method of encrypting data that is transmitted over your wireless network. This security measure is an IEEE standard. How it works: The wireless data is encrypted at the computer sending the data and is then decoded by the receiving computer. The WEP Key generated and duplicated on the wireless computers allows the computers and your gateway to communicate with one another. This encryption method allows users to have the same amount of security over their wireless network as they would over a wired network.</p><p>WPA (Wi-Fi Protected Access) is a standard that offers additional security features over WEP.  WPA is a next generation standard that is backward compatible with devices using WEP.  WPA features 2 technology improvements over WEP:</p><p>Improved encryption through the use of a key that automatically changes after a specific time interval.</p><p>To config the wireless security, the procedures are listed below.</p><p><b>For WEP configurations:</b></p><p>The <b>WEP Passphrase</b> feature can be used to automatically generate a <b>WEP Key</b>, which will be used to secure your wireless network. Choose a unique passphrase, enter it in the WEP Passphrase field, and press the Generate button. A passphrase is a personal password or phrase up to 31 alphanumeric characters (no spaces). This word or phrase will generate a 10 or 26 digit WEP Key, depending on the WEP Encryption Strength. The same passphrase must then be entered in each of the wireless computers to generate the exact same key. This will allow wireless communication to the gateway.</p><p>An alphanumeric 10 or 26 digit <b>WEP</b> Key will automatically populate when a <b>WEP Passphrase</b> is generated. If 128-bit WEP Encryption Strength is chosen, a 26-character key will populate in Key 1. If 64-bit WEP Encryption Strength is chosen, a 10-character key will populate in Keys 1-4.</p><p><b>For WPA configurations</b>:</p><p>Select whether you would like to utilize WPA with a pre-shared key.</p><p>For <b>WPA pre-shared key</b>, type the <b>Pass phrase</b> string.</p><p>Select which <b>WPA Algorithm</b> you would like to use:</p><p><b>TKIP (Temporal Key Integrity Protocol)</b> TKIP scrambles the keys with a hashing algorithm, and with an integrity-checking feature, ensures that the keys haven't been tampered with between the gateway and the wirelessly connected computer.</p><p><b>AES (Advanced Encryption Standard)</b> AES is a stronger encryption technique than TKIP.  However, AES may not work properly with some older wireless hardware.Wifi security mode will be WPA2-AES if wireless mode is 11N only.</p><hr/><h4>Button</h4><p>This <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" class=\"btn btn-primary\" title=\"Apply Button\" data-content=\"And here's some amazing content. It's very engaging. right?\">Save changes</a> should save the data and submit the form.</p><p>This <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" class=\"btn\" title=\"Cancel Button\" data-content=\"And here's some amazing content. It's very engaging. right?\">Cancel</a> should reset the all data.</p><p>This <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" class=\"btn\" title=\"Help Button\" data-content=\"And here's some amazing content. It's very engaging. right?\">Help</a> should show the configure guide.</p><br/></div>",

