"Admin_Remote_Help_Head":"Remote Management Setting Guide",
"Admin_Remote_Help_Body":"<h4>Introduction</h4><p>If users on the Internet want to remotely manage the device, there are two ways, telnet and web</p><br/><p>Remote Management allows the gateway to be remotely accessed by a customer account representative to perform troubleshooting or maintenance</p><p>Remote Management can be used via HTTP and HTTPS.</p><p>Enter the value for HTTP Port and click the button Enable, then you can access your device from HTTP. For example, if the WAN IP address is 11.22.11.22 and the HTTP port number is 8080, then you would use http://11.22.11.22:8080.It's the same way to configure HTTPS.Select whether you would like to have Remote management open to all internet IP addresses, an internet IP address range, or a single internet IP address.</p><p>After changing the settings, click the \"Save changes\" button to make the settings effective.</p><hr/><h4>Button</h4><p>This <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">Save changes</a> should save the data and submit the form.</p><p>This <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" class=\"btn\">Cancel</a> should reset the all data.</p><p>This <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" class=\"btn\">Help</a> should show the configure guide.</p><br/>",

