"Security_Service_Filter_Help_Body":"<h4>Introduction</h4><p>Service filtering is used to block certain outbound traffic which is destined to specific target port or port range from specific computers in the internal network.These rules will not take effect on the devices in the trusted PC list.</p><hr/><h4>Button</h4><p>This <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">Save changes</a> should save the data and submit the form.</p><p>This <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" class=\"btn btn-info\">Add Managed Device</a> or <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" class=\"btn btn-info\">Add Trust Device</a> should add the info of a device.</p><p>This <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn'>Manage</a> should edit the info of a device.</p><p>This <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn btn-danger'>Remove</a> should delete the info of a device.</p><p>This <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" class=\"btn\">Help</a> should show the configure guide.</p><br/>",
