"Security_Keyword_Filter_Help_Body":"<h4>Introduction</h4><p>You can configure which keyword and URL should be blocked here.</p><br/><p>First of all, if you want to set one or several keywords, click the <b>Enable</b> button, then type the keyword which you want to block, you can type the full URL,such like \"www.example.com\". Then the filter will block the website which use this URL or You can type a part of URL ,such like \"sex\" ,then the filter will block the website which its URL include this string and then choose the time, finally click the <b>Add</b> button.</p><hr/><h4>Button</h4><p>This <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn btn-info'>Add Trust Device</a> should add the info of a new trust device.</p><p>This <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn btn-primary'>Save changes</a> should save the data and submit the form.</p><p>This <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn'>Manage</a> should edit the info of the trust device.</p><p>This <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn btn-danger'>Remove</a> should delete the info of a trust device.</p><p>This <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn'>Help</a> should show the configure guide.</p><br/>",

