"Advanced_Route_Help_Body":"<h4>Introduction</h4><p>Static routes provide the routing information for routes connected to the LAN.</p><br/><p>Users may set up the static route rule to cable.</p><p>the static rule will influence the data which contains Destination IP forwarding.</p><p>the data will then be forwarded to the Gateway IP you have defined.</p><p>After all are defined, click the Apply button to make all features take effect.</p><hr/><h4>Button</h4><p>This <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn btn-primary'>Save changes</a> should save the data and submit the form.</p><p>This <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn btn-info'>Add</a> should add a new rule.</p><p>This <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn'>Manage</a> should edit a rule.</p><p>This <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn btn-danger'>Remove</a> should delete a rule.</p><p>This <a href='javascript:void(0);' class='btn'>Help</a> should show the configure guide.</p>",

