"Advanced_Rip_Help_Body":"<h4>Introduction</h4><p>The device uses the RIP protocol to provide the dynamic routes.</p><br/><p>Users may set up the RIP control to each interface and define the authentication method if necessary.</p><p>Usually the RIP protocol is broadcasted or multicasted.</p><p>To unicast the protocol to a specific router, define the IP address in the Neighbour row.</p><p>After all RIP control functions are defined, click the Apply button to make all features take effect.</p><hr/><h4>Button</h4><p>This <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" class=\"btn btn-primary\" title=\"Apply Button\" data-content=\"And here's some amazing content. It's very engaging. right?\">Save changes</a> should save the data and submit the form.</p><p>This <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" class=\"btn\" title=\"Cancel Button\" data-content=\"And here's some amazing content. It's very engaging. right?\">Cancel</a> should reset the all data.</p><p>This <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" class=\"btn\" title=\"Help Button\" data-content=\"And here's some amazing content. It's very engaging. right?\">Help</a> should show the configure guide.</p><br/>",

