"Advanced_Speedtest_Help_Body":"<h4>Introduce</h4><p>The device 's WAN speed can be tested by this SpeedTest Application, the test procedure will test download speed first, then upload test.</p><hr/><h4>Configure</h4><p>As the SpeedTest Application is based on C/S model, we should specify an Ookla Server.</p><p>The Ookla Server Address input filed is to configure Ookla Server, may be DomainName or IpAddress.</p><p>Specially, if you don't specify an Server, the Application will download a configure file named speedtest-servers.php from http://www.speedtest.net, which list about two thousand ookla servers infomation,</p>then choose five closer servers to your ISP according of server's longitude and latitude information, then download latancy from each server among these five servers, choose the best server based on speed of downloading latency.</p><p>After all configuration are defined, click the Start Test button to lanch test procedure.</p><hr/><h4>Button</h4><p>This <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" class=\"btn btn-info\">Start Test</a> should start speed test.</p><p>This <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" class=\"btn\">Help</a> should show the configure guide.</p><br/>",

